(school bell rings)

03:29.103 --> 03:31.503
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wha-What's
happening? What are you doing?

03:31.537 --> 03:32.671
Hey, there, Lumps.

03:32.705 --> 03:34.425
Just taking advantage
of the high ceilings

03:34.426 --> 03:36.325
on this, my new rehearsal space.

03:36.359 --> 03:38.576
It is now the home of my
brand-new French-Canadian,

03:38.594 --> 03:42.580
circus-inspired Cheerios!
Side project, Sue du Soleil.

03:42.598 --> 03:44.118
Get rid of all this sparkly red stuff.

03:44.169 --> 03:45.929
It still smells like
the Glee Club in here.

03:45.930 --> 03:47.252
What are you talking about?

03:47.270 --> 03:48.753
Well, when your season ended,

03:48.771 --> 03:50.088
with your loss at Sectionals,

03:50.106 --> 03:51.861
I filed the appropriate paperwork

03:51.862 --> 03:54.142
so that the Cheerios! Take
full possession of this room,

03:54.193 --> 03:56.594
including everything
in it... your trophies,

03:56.612 --> 03:59.931
your beloved plaque
with the late Lillian Adler.

03:59.966 --> 04:02.701
And I took her inspirational quotation,

04:02.735 --> 04:05.037
and I re-engraved something
for myself here.

04:05.071 --> 04:07.605
"I died a slow, horrible death
choking on the fluid

04:07.623 --> 04:09.791
in my own lungs."

04:12.328 --> 04:13.996
You...

04:14.030 --> 04:16.882
You can't do this.
Oh, I didn't do this.

04:16.916 --> 04:19.051
You did this, and now
if you'll excuse me,

04:19.084 --> 04:21.553
I'm going to take
your Nationals trophy,

04:21.587 --> 04:24.056
and I'm going to run
over it with my Le Car.

04:25.758 --> 04:28.010
Over my dead body.

04:32.098 --> 04:33.965
(grunting)

04:33.983 --> 04:35.967
Figgins' office.

04:35.985 --> 04:37.986
Now!

04:41.107 --> 04:42.324
Door jam?

04:42.358 --> 04:43.808
(school bell ringing)

04:43.826 --> 04:45.327
How could you have let this happen?

04:45.361 --> 04:46.978
It's not rocket science, Will.

04:46.996 --> 04:49.581
When the football team
loses and the season is over,

04:49.615 --> 04:52.084
they are longer entitled
to use the field!

04:52.118 --> 04:53.651
Fine. We'll use
the auditorium.

04:53.669 --> 04:54.836
The auditorium now belongs

04:54.871 --> 04:56.872
to the McKinley High
Drum and Bugle Corps.

04:56.923 --> 04:58.206
What about the Spanish Room?

04:58.257 --> 04:59.777
I've rented it out to the Rotary Club.

04:59.778 --> 05:01.978
The history classroom? Sex
and Love Addicts Anonymous.

05:01.979 --> 05:03.499
You're telling me that there's nowhere

05:03.500 --> 05:05.420
in this school
that the Glee Club can rehearse?

05:05.454 --> 05:07.454
That's exactly what
I'm telling you, Finn Hudson.

05:07.455 --> 05:08.666
It's pure economics.

05:08.684 --> 05:11.720
The district is running
a seven-figure deficit,

05:11.754 --> 05:13.555
and we're sitting on prime real estate.

05:13.606 --> 05:15.507
SUE:
Let's face facts.

05:15.525 --> 05:17.008
The New Directions!
Are finished.

05:17.026 --> 05:18.843
You have no place
to practice or perform.

05:18.861 --> 05:20.817
The only thing left
to do is to hand over

05:20.818 --> 05:22.898
the keys to the choir room
and inform your students

05:22.949 --> 05:25.200
that Glee Club is over for the year.

05:25.234 --> 05:27.354
And if that's too much
for your feeble constitution,

05:27.370 --> 05:28.887
I'm happy to do it for you.

05:30.123 --> 05:32.290
No.

05:32.325 --> 05:35.710
I'll do it.

05:36.712 --> 05:38.964
(school bell ringing)

05:38.998 --> 05:41.083
(sighs)

05:41.134 --> 05:42.300
How does it feel, Coach?

05:42.335 --> 05:45.036
Got to be honest, Becky.

05:45.054 --> 05:47.722
I have looked forward
to this very moment

05:47.757 --> 05:49.641
for a long time.

05:49.675 --> 05:51.709
Now that it's finally here,

05:51.727 --> 05:55.714
I'm left with a strange, empty feeling.

05:55.748 --> 05:58.650
That's how I felt
when I saw <i>Prometheus.</i>

05:58.684 --> 06:00.552
Now, I'd be lying if I said

06:00.570 --> 06:02.604
I wasn't a little concerned
about them, Becky.

06:02.655 --> 06:04.556
(sighs)

06:04.574 --> 06:09.394
Those Glee Clubbers are
so emotionally fragile,

06:09.412 --> 06:12.564
I can't help wonder
what this will do to them.

06:12.582 --> 06:14.583
With their dreams crushed,

06:14.617 --> 06:16.901
where and who will they be

06:16.919 --> 06:19.237
in just a few short months?

06:19.255 --> 06:21.739
I'm a drug mule
in the Lima crack district.

06:21.757 --> 06:23.658
I was forced to sell my legs
to science.

06:23.693 --> 06:25.333
I'm performing
on the bathhouse circuit.

06:25.334 --> 06:27.345
I'm a finance major at Brandeis.

06:27.380 --> 06:30.081
It turns out Glee Club
was really holding me back.

06:30.099 --> 06:33.135
Oh, I wish there was some way
to assuage my guilt.

06:33.186 --> 06:35.520
A sign that I was doing
the right thing.

06:35.555 --> 06:37.305
(knocking)

06:37.356 --> 06:39.758
Sue Sylvester?
I cannot thank you enough.

06:39.792 --> 06:42.677
I can't tell you
how much I hate those kids!

06:42.712 --> 06:45.090
Do you know how demeaning
it is when they just turn to you

06:45.091 --> 06:46.931
and yell, "Hit it!,"
and you're just supposed

06:46.949 --> 06:48.600
to know what song they're gonna sing?

06:48.618 --> 06:50.268
I'm free. Free.

06:50.286 --> 06:52.604
(school bell ringing)

06:52.638 --> 06:54.089
So, that's it?

06:54.123 --> 06:55.874
No more Glee? Until
next September.

06:55.908 --> 06:57.042
Sugar already bailed.

06:57.076 --> 06:59.044
Can I just say
what everyone is thinking?

06:59.078 --> 07:00.878
This is Marley's fault.
New Rachel, my butt.

07:00.880 --> 07:02.547
I knew Rachel Berry.

07:02.582 --> 07:03.999
I was friends with Rachel Berry,

07:04.050 --> 07:05.950
and you, Marley, are no Rachel Berry.
Mm-hmm.

07:05.968 --> 07:07.952
Preach. FINN: Guys,
guys, enough.

07:07.970 --> 07:10.362
It's not like it's over.
The holiday concert is later

07:10.363 --> 07:12.123
this week, and we are
going to be preparing

07:12.141 --> 07:13.391
for it all week long.

07:13.426 --> 07:15.393
If this is our swan song,

07:15.428 --> 07:17.629
let's make it the best one it can be.

07:17.647 --> 07:18.904
You really expect us to go up

07:18.905 --> 07:20.465
in front of the whole school and parade

07:20.483 --> 07:21.966
our loserdom for all to see?

07:21.984 --> 07:23.184
Yeah, Kitty does have a point.

07:23.185 --> 07:24.825
We agreed to do the show
when we thought

07:24.826 --> 07:27.066
it would be on the heels
of another Sectionals victory.

07:27.067 --> 07:28.573
Now it just feels like a pity party.

07:28.608 --> 07:30.733
I love to sing and dance
as much as anybody,

07:30.734 --> 07:32.694
but without a competition
to prep for, it's hard

07:32.728 --> 07:33.578
to get motivated.

07:33.613 --> 07:34.812
I understand that we need

07:34.830 --> 07:36.239
a little shift in perspective,

07:36.240 --> 07:38.200
but let's just enjoy this week,
and look forward

07:38.251 --> 07:40.318
to our big comeback next year.
That's right.

07:40.336 --> 07:42.454
What about those of us
who won't have a next year?

07:46.442 --> 07:48.426
(school bell ringing)

08:21.504 --> 08:23.371
It worked.
You found me.

08:23.389 --> 08:26.007
Did you lay out the
line of cereal for me?

08:26.008 --> 08:27.208
Well, it's Tuesday, and I know

08:27.209 --> 08:28.969
how you forget
to eat breakfast on Tuesdays

08:28.970 --> 08:31.330
'cause the first few days
of the week tend to confuse you.

08:31.331 --> 08:32.211
How did you know that?

08:32.212 --> 08:33.315
You told me.

08:34.900 --> 08:36.717
Is that mine? I think
maybe the reason

08:36.751 --> 08:39.256
why Santana was always
picking on me was because

08:39.258 --> 08:40.538
some part of her knew the truth.

08:40.573 --> 08:42.107
About Area 51?

08:42.158 --> 08:45.226
About that I'm totally into you.

08:45.261 --> 08:48.330
You're, uh, the only person
that really understands me.

08:48.364 --> 08:50.115
It's 'cause you're a genius.

08:50.166 --> 08:52.066
And most people don't
understand geniuses.

08:52.084 --> 08:54.068
Like most people
didn't appreciate Einstein

08:54.086 --> 08:56.071
or the Spice Girls
until it was too late.

08:56.105 --> 08:58.072
And I think that you know that I think

08:58.090 --> 09:01.926
that you are... pretty awesome.

09:01.961 --> 09:03.345
And your impressions are amazing.

09:03.379 --> 09:05.019
(like Elvis):
Well, thank you, Brittany.

09:05.020 --> 09:06.020
(laughs) I'm super bummed

09:06.021 --> 09:07.915
